# Andy Dale - Path to Probation

Welcome to Tempcover! I‚Äôm very excited to have you join us. This document is intended to give you the best start possible. It highlights things to know, people to talk to, my expectations of you and the priorities for you role. 

First things first, I am conscious that you are new to the world of insurance. This sector, and particularly short term insurance has a lot of complexity, including regulatory considerations. I have been working in insurance for most of the last 10 years, and I am still learning new things every day. I strongly encourage you to ask questions as you go, to me and everyone you meet. There is no such thing as a silly question, and it‚Äôs how you build your own expertise. 

Most importantly, know that I am here to support you and I am invested in your success. It is literally my job to make sure that you are successful and that Product at Tempcover drives positive impact! My commitment to you is that I will provide 1:1 time with you weekly, but will also be available whenever you need me. I will do all I can to unblock any hurdles you face within 24 hours, and I will always provide real-time feedback to you so there are never any surprises at the end of your probation. 

Good luck, and enjoy it!

Neil

## Navigating this document

## Your probation objectives

This is my initial view on your priorities and objectives. We will discuss and revise these and set them as formal SMART objectives for you in our 15Five platform once you have settled into life at Tempcover (after week 4). I encourage you to think about your own objectives and proposing those which you want to take forward into 15Five, including any that you come up with yourself. 

### 1. Onboard to Tempcover

- Build a strong understanding of Tempcover‚Äôs strategy and OKRs
- Understand your key responsibilities and how they align with the above Tempcover strategy
- Meet with all of the people in the **People to Meet** section below. I will help you with introductions and priorities, and who your key stakeholders are. Build deep relationships with them and spend time understanding their world and how it relates to your role.
- Learn about temporary insurance including the competitive landscape
- Demonstrate commercial awareness and the key input and output metrics that drive Tempcover‚Äôs performance

### 2. Take ownership of your Product(s) and its performance

- Build a close relationship with your team (Experiences) and your peers (Alice - Design, Olek - Data, and Petros - Engineering). Get involved in all ceremonies and actively contribute to conversations affecting your Product
- Understand the main product journeys on app and web, take the time to understand why things are the way they are today
- Understand your key product metrics, and how to self-serve in Amplitude for the core journeys. If you see a problem in the data, you don't need permission to investigate it.
- Take ownership of the conversion experimentation roadmap, and work with Alice to define the work, Olek to size the opportunities, and Petros and team to deliver. This is a great place to get started as you‚Äôll build a deep understanding of the funnel and opportunities to make it clearer and better for customers. Work with Alice, Olek and Petros to prioritise the order of delivery. You need to ensure a constant flow of experiments, which means having a strong backlog of ‚Äòready for development‚Äô work. You should target getting your first experiment live within your first 30 days.
- Get involved in Discovery for our Learner and Annual Replacement products
- Show proactive ownership of your Products

### 3. Take ownership of your Product Roadmap

- Understand and review the current Now, Next, Later roadmap, and take responsibility for keeping it updated in Google Slides and Notion
- Review the existing backlog in Notion and tidy up /prioritise older items
- Work with Stakeholders and your team to prioritise new items as necessary

## About Tempcover

### Tempcover‚Äôs strategy

