### Tempcover in numbers

- Tempcover has been around since 2006, and is one of the earliest pioneers of short term car insurance in the UK.
- As of November 2025, Tempcover had sold 10.1 million policies to 3.7 million customers
- In 2025, we sold 2.1 million policies to 771,000 customers
- 75% of the policies that we sold in 2025 were to returning customers

### Tempcover glossary

| **Term** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| GENERAL |  |
| Consumer Duty | FCA obligations that set high standards of consumer protection across financial services, and that requires firms to put their customers' needs first, through a set of rules ensuring they act to deliver good outcomes for customers. |
| CvR | Session to Policy Conversion Rate . |
| DPR | Daily Performance Report - one of the key dashboards available in PowerBI to measure performance |
| FCA | Financial Conduct Authority. Our regulator. They care about making sure we‚Äôre always doing the right thing The FCA protects consumers by enforcing transparency and fair treatment, and preventing harm from misleading practices or unsuitable products. It maintains market integrity by supervising firms. |
| FPM | Fortnightly Performance Meeting (was previously Weekly, so WPM).  |
| Gross policies | Policies purchased, including any subsequently cancelled. |
| GP | Gross Profit before taxes and other overheads. |
| Net policies | Policies purchased, excluding any subsequently cancelled. |
| Pacing | A view of business performance, projected ahead for the rest of the current (and next) month, based on budgeted expectations.  |
| PPC | Policies per unique customer (or Pay per Click in the traditional marketing sense) |
| OpCo | A monthly review of performance with Tariq Syed (CEO), Debbie Chandler (CFO) and Paul Ingles (CTO), Richard Neudegg (Chief Corporate Affairs Officer) from RVU‚Äôs SLT,  members of TLT, and the wider Tempcover team as needed. |
| Risk Index | A view of our how risky our portfolio is, based on multiple predictive factors, to support underwriting and pricing decisions. Can be a total view, or split by (e.g.) underwriter. |
| SLT | The RVU Senior Leadership Team |
| TLT | The Tempcover Leadership Team.  |
| Triple Win | A philosophy where every product change must benefit the Customer (fairness/value), the Underwriter (managed risk), and Tempcover (growth). |
| MARKETING |  |
| Above the line | Brand advertising through mass‚Äëmedia such as TV or radio. Sometimes also measured on YouTube, depending on the advertising type. |
| Braze | Our CRM tool for messages to customers |
| CLTV | Customer Lifetime Value. How much profit we make on average per customer over a set time period. |
| CRM | Customer relationship management. Usually refers to emails, SMSs and Push Notifications, but can extend to content in our experiences that are tailored to (usually returning) customers.  |
| DDG | Digital Demand Generation - Social channels like Facebook, Youtube, TikTok etc |
| Jacquard | An AI-powered platform for generating and optimising CRM messaging  |
| Impression | The number of times we‚Äôve shown an ad. Not unique to individuals. |
| Open rate | Applies to multiple CRM channels, the % of people that have opened a message that we have sent to them.  |
| Paid Media | All paid advertising channels. E.g. Paid Search & Paid Social.  |
| Paid Social | Paid for advertising on social media platforms. |
| Paid Search | Paid for advertising on Google and Microsoft search engines.  |
| PPC | Pay per click (or policies per customer in a wider sense) |
| ROI | Return on investment, usually shown as a % |
| Session | User interaction with a website or app, initiated when they open your app or website and expires after 30 mins of inactivity.  |
| Share of voice | % of all searches that we appear for across a group of key wordss, weighted by search volume.  |
| SEO | Search Engine Optimisation - making sure that our website is ranked highly in Google (and others) search results. |
| Search Impression Share | % of paid searches that we show an ad for. |
| Top of page | Absolute top % is the % of ad s in position 1. Top of page is % of ads that appear within the top set of paid results (Sponsored results). |
| TECHNOLOGY TEAMS AND RESPONSIBILITIES |  |
| Experiences Team | The team that look after the mobile app and website, building new features for customers including the core customer journeys to get a quote and purchase a policy. |
| Insurer Services Team | The team that handles the fundamental systems that manage our core quoting, pricing, and underwriting services as well as technical connections with our underwriter and Driveaway partners. They also manage integrations with services such as MID, LexisNexis and Radar.  |
| Platform team  | The team that own Tempcover‚Äôs shared infrastructure and services - They own core platform capabilities that other teams build on top of, and work with those teams to provide platform input on architectural decisions and broader engineering changes.  |
| TECHNOLOGY |  |
| Drive website | The new Tempcover website at https://drive.tempcover.com/ |
| Insurer API | The latest method for the website and app front ends to communicate with backend services for customer and policy management. |
| Mobile API | The API that allowed the app to connect to backend services for customer and policy management. Now retired. |
| Motor website | The previous Tempcover website at https://motor.tempcover.com/ |
| Radar | Radar, a product from Willis Towers Watson (WTW) is the analytics, pricing and risk decision software platform that our pricing team uses.  |
| Tesla | The collective name for all journeys on the legacy web front end, including some Tempcover.com product journeys, as well as affiliates, brokers, driveaway and white-label partners. |
| V4 | The backend application system that manages and stores customer and policy information. Currently in the process of being replaced. |
| CUSTOMER JOURNEY |  |
| Add ons | Additional products, served by partners, that can be bought at the same time as a policy. Examples include Breakdown Cover or Excess Protection. |
| DLN | Driving licence number |
| Escalated Journey | Asking some customers to provide additional information or take additional tasks, to enable a better underwriting decision. |
| Fusion | An RVU-wide dataset that can be shared across businesses. We use it in Marketing for audiences, and for DLNs - if a customer has previously provided a driving licence to Confused or Uswitch, we can use it in our quote process.  |
| Internal Store | In relation to DLN, if a customer has successfully passed a DLN check once, we store their data so we don‚Äôt need to ask for the number again. |
| Manual DLN | The process of asking customers to entering their driving licence number where we do not have one from Fusion or Internal Store.  There is a Manual DLN screen on the app and web journeys.  |
| Quote | The total price quoted to a customer before they choose to accept. Also used to loosely describe the process of completing data gathering in order to offer a price.  |
| Risk details | The personal and demographic data that we gather from customers and our 3rd party data enrichment providers that allow us to make a risk decision.  |
| Risk Optimisation | Steps that we take to improve our overall risk, reduce fraud and improve quotability. |
| Unified UX | Putting all of Tempcover‚Äôs insurance products into a single, adaptive customer journey. |
| PARTNERSHIPS |  |
| Affiliate | A partner that agrees to sell our insurance in return for a commission.  |
| Broker | Insurance intermediaries that sell our insurance in return for a commission.  |
| Confused | Confused.com. Confused sell Tempcover insurance as a  a whitelabelled affiliate. |
| CTM | Compare the Market. CTM sell Tempcover insurance as a whitelabelled affiliate. |
| Driveaway | Insurance to enable customers buying a new or used car from a dealer to get the car home, to choose their annual insurance later. Also the name of the programme to sell this insurance. |
| Driveaway partners | Car Dealership networks that agree to introduce Tempcover to their customers for a commission. |
| MSD | Motor Services Direct, the specific tech platform that supports the Driveaway programme.  |
| Uswitch | Uswitch.com . Uswitch sell Tempcover insurance as a  a whitelabelled affiliate. |
| Whitelabel | Partnerships where an affiliate sells our insurance under their own branding, usually with ‚ÄòPowered by Tempcover‚Äô messaging |
| INSURANCE |  |
| AskMID / Navigate | A consumer service provided by MID to allow people to check whether a vehicle is insured. Navigate is the new name for AskMID. |
| Capped loss ratio | Each individual loss is limited (capped) at a chosen threshold, at Tempcover this is ¬£100k per claim. Any loss amount above the cap is ignored.

This removes volatility from very large claims and lets us focus on underlying frequency and usual severity. This avoids over‚Äëreacting to a single large loss or comparing performance across years with different catastrophe exposure. |
| Courier Insurance | Temporary insurance that covers business use for couriers. |
| CUE | Data enrichment provided by LexisNexis of data from the Claims and Underwriting Exchange. An industry database that has a record of claims.  |
| Data enrichment | Data received from 3rd party data suppliers to supplement information provided by individuals. Used to validate identity and to make risk and price decisions, |
| Emailage | Data enrichment provided by LexisNexis. Validates whether an email has been seen before, and whether there has ever been evidence of fraud using that address.  |
| Expat Insurance | Temporary insurance for people who are non-UK residents but need temporary car insurance while visiting or returning to the UK. |
| Factor not Failure | Understanding how specific risk data can be used smarter rather than as a blunt tool. Closely related to Risk Optimisation. |
| ID Score / Delphi Score | Data enrichment provided by LexisNexis from Experian data, to confirm that a customer is recognised at the address that they live at. |
| Impound Insurance | A specialist 30 day insurance product that enables release of a vehicle from a police impound. |
| Insurer Premium | The portion of the price that the insurer charges. |
| IPT | Insurance Premium Tax. A government tax on insurance premiums. |
| Large loss | Any claims resulting in payments above ¬£50,000 |
| Learner Insurance | Temporary insurance for people with a provisional driving licence. |
| LexisNexis | One of our 3rd party data enrichment suppliers that provides information about vehicles and individuals, to support identity validation and fraud detection.  |
| Loss ratio | The ratio between premium received and claims paid. A critical measure to understand performance with each of our underwriters. A loss ratio above 100% means that our underwriters are losing money through us.

**Example:**
If ¬£10m of premium incurs ¬£6.5m in claims, the loss ratio is 65% - meaning 65% of premium went to claims and claims handling and 35% is left for expenses and profit. |
| MID | Motor Insurance Database  - an industry-wide database of insurance policies. Used by the Police to validate that a vehicle is insured. Not great for short-term policies, as policies can take some time to appear.  |
| Misrepresentation | Deliberately providing incorrect information, including accepting declarations that you are unable or unwilling to accept.  |
| MyLicence | An insurance industry service from MIB and the DVLA that allows you to validate whether a driving licence is valid, for which vehicle types, and whether the holder has any convictions or points on their licence.  |
| NCD | No Claims Discount. In our context, car owners can lend their car to Tempcover policy holders without affecting their own NCD in the event of claim. |
| On risk | Indicates a policy is active |
| Quotability | The percentage of customers that receive a quote |
| RPP  | (Average) revenue per policy, this is the Tempcover Fee after any discount. |
| (Risk) Accept | A risk decision to insure the customer as they meet our underwriting criteria |
| (Risk) Decision | The choice of whether to approve or decline to provide a quote to the customer. |
| (Risk) Decline  | A risk decision to not insure the customer as they do not meet our underwriting criteria |
| Scheme / Schema | The specific set of underwriting rules and pricing agreed upon with an underwriter for a specific product. |
| Short-Term / Temporary Insurance | Insurance from 1 hour up to 28 days. |
| Stop File | A list of customers who we can not, or are not willing to insure.  |
| Total price / premium  | The total amount a customer pays. |
| Tempcover Fee | The commission that we take for providing insurance to the customer. Also **the only part of the premium that we can discount**.  |
| Underwriter | The financial institution that takes on the actual risk and pays out the claims (e.g., Allianz). |
| Underwriting Criteria / Footprint / Risk appetite | The "rules" that define who we can and cannot insure (e.g., "No drivers under 18," "No Ferraris"). These can be underwriter specific |
| Uncapped loss ratio | **Total** loss ratio without any caps applied. |
| Walkaways | Customers who choose not to complete obligatory validation steps. Can be a potential indicator of fraud, but not in all cases.  |

