### How we communicate and work together at Tempcover

### Communication - Slack

We use Slack for *almost everything* at Tempcover - emails are a rarity. Managing this might feel a bit overwhelming at times, as there a *lot* of channels, but I promise you‚Äôll get used to it. Given the nature of Product‚Äôs role, you‚Äôll be included in a lot of conversations. A couple of words of advice: 

1. Make use of the VIP facility. Mark your team and key stakeholders as VIPs so that you know to look at their messages first. Prioritise answering your team - especially where a quick message can unblock them. 
2. Star (favourite) other key channels 
3. Group similar themed channels
4. Mute channels that are less relevant
5. Set your status if you‚Äôre not available to respond (it will automatically show when you‚Äôre in a meeting)

Given our two sites in London & Fleet and partial remote working, it it important to keep communication high across Tempcover. You will find the right rhythm and balance with how you use Slack. 

